<p>@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<h1 class="text-center">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<div class="container mt-4">
    <h3>Overview</h3>
    <p>
        This website is a personal engineering portfolio created and maintained by Billy J. Louis III.
        Its purpose is to showcase professional experience, projects, certificates, and related work.
    </p>

    <h3>Data Collection</h3>
    <p>
        This site does <strong>not</strong> collect personal information from visitors.
        No forms, accounts, or tracking systems are used.
    </p>
    <p>
        The only data automatically collected is standard, non‑identifiable web server information such as:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Browser type</li>
        <li>Operating system</li>
        <li>Approximate device resolution</li>
        <li>Basic traffic logs</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        This information is generated automatically by the hosting platform and is used only for performance and security monitoring.
    </p>

    <h3>Cookies</h3>
    <p>
        This site does <strong>not</strong> use cookies for tracking, analytics, advertising, or personalization.
        Any cookies present are default, temporary technical cookies required by the hosting platform.
    </p>

    <h3>External Links</h3>
    <p>
        This website contains links to external platforms such as GitHub, LinkedIn, a chip design portfolio, and PDF certificates.
        These external sites have their own privacy policies. Once you leave this site, their policies apply.
    </p>

    <h3>Security</h3>
    <p>
        The site is hosted on Microsoft Azure App Service, which provides encrypted HTTPS connections,
        platform‑level security, and automatic updates. No visitor data is stored or processed by this site.
    </p>

    <h3>Contact</h3>
    <p>
        For questions about this privacy policy or the website, you may reach out through my
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/billy-louis-a3196964/" target="_blank">LinkedIn profile</a>.
    </p>

    <p class="text-muted mt-4">
        <em>Last updated: @DateTime.Now.ToString("MMMM yyyy")</em>
    </p>
</div></p>
